Love love loved it. I got the lemongrass chicken bowl with veggies and rice, added the red Thai sauce  The flavors were rich, veggies were fresh, the ground chicken was yummy. Excellent food! Not disappointed at all. We had the Chef Bills Special and were pleasantly satisfied with the food combination and the taste.  Also, the fries are tasty along with the sauce it comes with. I will definitely visit again the next time I'm in Chicago.

Urbanbelly is super delicious. The staff is super friendly. Once you place your order your food arrives to you fresh and hot within minutes. The food portions are big to me, which is a plus. Literally everything on the menu is super tasty and rich in flavors. Occasionally I will see the owner helping out. From cleaning the tables, helping the kitchen, and I’m sure more. I gave this restaurant a chance because I saw all the great reviews.  I ordered the chicken katsu fried rice and udon.  There was one overpowering seasoning in both dishes that overpowered both dishes, not sure if it was curry, garlic, or a type of radish, maybe saffron.  In any case, the chicken was also super soggy.  I also ordered the fries and did not realize it would be spicy as well as super soggy.  I spent $55 and ended up throwing the food away, definitely wasted, but I guess at least now I know and won't be ordering from here again.

Training of Maxican officials working on site is required, they are veryoooo Rude. The Kitchen is to be congratulated always deliver the food on time at the time marked in the application. Fair price.

A really solid Asian-fusion restaurant. Ramen is my weakness so I'm glad to get something not only very tasty but very filling here. There are other places that are comparable but the selection is very solid and the prices are good.

I originally wanted to try Urbanbelly because of an add I saw for their “Thai fried chicken” on Instagram. The fact that they sold ramen too was the kicker, I had to go. I ordered for pick up and this is what I received. The Thai fried chicken was sub par meat chicken nuggets, basically some frozen Tyson type stuff. They were mushy too. The sauce was in a little cup on the side.  Also, if your a ramen fan this place will not excite you. Out of the last dozen places I’ve had for ramen this is the only bowl I didn’t want to finish.  I’m always willing to give restaurants second chances but I’m not in a rush. Maybe something else on there menu is good but I won’t be ordering the ramen or Thai chicken
Great for delivery! They package everything up perfectly so that you don't get a plastic bag full of sauce once it arrives. And the Tom Kha soup is fantastic!
Cute place. Ramen was really good as well as the rice bowl. They have happy hour and a bunch of other nonalcoholic drinks. Will be returning!

The spice has a great kick to it but not too much where you’ll need to chug water. They come seasoned too, so that just makes them even better if spicy isn’t your thing. The curry bowls are very good, and had a nice balance of all ingredients. Also, the mixed drinks are unique and fun. Definitely would go again!

Heard about The House for years and somehow never got around to going until last week.  My friends and I shared 3 entrees - sea bass, steak, and a special at the time I believe it was halibut in cream sauce. They were all very delicious! Especially the fish dishes.  We also had a mushroom soup, which was average. And their famous salmon rolls for appetizer. It was great! The salmon is half seared so the inside is still tender and fresh.  Overall we had a great time here although I have to say the portions are just a tiny bit small for me. I'd give this place a solid 4 stars. I do find it perhaps a little bit overhyped but
Dumplings and chicken krinchi on fried rice were amazing my parents loved this place. will come back again

Everything on the menu is delicious, doesn't matter how many times you have it.  It never gets old and you can never just have one thing.  The staff all love and care about the food and go above and beyond to make you feel at home - especially Monica (love her!!).  And then on top of it, we even get to rub elbows with the famous Chef Bill Kim who owns the restaurant!  Buy the book too while you're there to learn how to make these awesome dishes at home, especially for you grill masters.  Phat Style Fried Pineapple Rice...YUM.  THE RAMEN...YUM...The dumplings.  The kimchi fries.  I hope you're drooling cause I am if you couldn't tell....

This place is described as an unpretentious Asian Fusion restaurant. I said “why not” I’m craving ramen let’s see what they’ve got.  So there is one ramen dish on the menu and let me tell you they have mastered it. It was perfect! A whole soft boiled egg cooked to perfection. Not one but two pieces of pork belly. Just the right amount of spice, it didn’t burn but you can feel it. I loved every bite. If they’ve taken this much care with their ramen I imagine their other dishes are just as good. So two thumbs up.
Delicious and great portions. Dumplings a tad small and overpriced.

Recently I visited Chicago, just for 3 days as a family trip! We tried this place on our second day of the trip! We were in the neighborhood looking for a good place to eat and saw this place and decided to walk in! We ordered urban bowl with lemongrass chicken, chicken dumplings and curry bowl with chicken katsu and passion fruit lemonade! OMG the food is soooo goood!!! Honestly it was one of the best Asian food places we have been to! The urban bowl with lemongrass chicken is the most delicious! We ordered this twice ! I can eat that bowl the whole day, it was that good! We decided to try this place again on our last day of the trip Bcz honestly out of the all the food places we tried this was the best! Their service is really friendly and everything is nicely organized! It’s a place with lots of seating arrangements! And the drink was refillable! Sooo worth the money! If you’re visiting Chicago , this place should be a MUST VISIT!! I’m just upset that they only have one location in USA! They should definitely open up more locations around the USA, atleast in NYC! I would probably then go there everyday! If I ever go back to Chicago again, I’ll have lunch and dinner there again for sure ! I love this place! It deserves 5 stars !! 👌🏼👌🏼👌🏼

I love Urban Belly.  It is one of the most consistently good restaurants I have been to and we will continue to go back.  My son craves the kids noodle soup weekly, so we literally have to get it for him or he’ll snap and keep asking everyday until we satisfy the craving.  I love the coconut pho, the curry bowl, and cold peanut noodles.  My only suggestion would be more specials and variety because I want to taste more delicious creations by Bill Kim!  However, this may be because my son is wrangling us there so often.  Overall, we are pleased and appreciate the consistency.

I look forward to going back to Urbanbelly and having a great experience like I have in the past. Thank you!  My order was wrong. I ordered phat rice bowl and instead I received a kids chicken and rice. I asked for a hot tea and they didn’t have any so then I was refunded. I wasn’t even given my receipt. I just did not have a good experience. The food was Fine but not spectacular. I had Ramen bowl and my husband had Thai chicken appetizer. My noodles came out uncooked- I requested that they cook it longer. The second time around was better but not great. I did like the broth but I love cilantro. It was definitely fusion and not traditional! My husband’s Thai appetizer just tasted deep fried and sweet/ sticky. No real flavor. There were fruit flies swarming our food the whole time. And I didn’t find the service appealing. They come set the food in front of you and walk away. Would have been nice if they would have mentioned where utensils/ napkins where. There was no spoons for the ramen- I saw them but they were way out of reach. Easy location, nice decor. I am not local so I probably won’t try it again but if I lived in the neighborhood I would probably give it one more go....

Overall my experiences here have been positive. I really enjoy the chicken katsu rice (dumpling?) soup as the perfect soothing and warming meal. I grew up in Japan, so katsu is a comfort food for me. The broth is a little spicy but very reasonably so and full of flavor. I am super glad that the Belly Dog is here, as it was my favorite item at Belly Shack when it was still around. The passionfruit lemonade is delicious and a perfect compliment to the meal. The potstickers are pretty tasty and probably the most kid-friendly item on the menu, if you have kids and want to take them there. The soft serve is also quite nice and comes in a parfait dish that helps elevate the treat. I wish they would bring back their yuzu lemonade that used to alternate with the passionfruit, but I suppose you can't have everything.

Love how you can just pop in, grab a few dumplings to go, and be on your way. More similar to the Asian street food style.  My one complaint is that I ordered three dumplings, and each one came in its own plastic container. Seems wasteful.

Our whole party enjoyed this place and wish we had  one at home in Vegas! Great lunch spot.

This review is for the Revival food court location. I ordered the chicken with rice and a water for $17.28. The attendant auto selected an 18% tip, and when I thought that was uncalled for on a take out lunch order, she gave me an attitude. Then I was not given the water that I paid for. The flavor of the chicken wasn't bad, however, it had a texture that made me think it had already been chewed. The rice was dried out as if it had been sitting out too long. On top of all of that, I was sick after the meal. I think this place has some serious mismanagement concerns that will cause it to go out of business if the issues are not addressed. Everything other than the cashier was bad. Their mezcal drink didn’t taste like there was any booze. Their dumplings are a joke; super small and more like potstickers. And the phat style’s meat quality, especially the beef, was really bad. $60 spent and that’ll be the last.
The food was good something different, can't  beat it.

I ordered the curry bowl with lemongrass chicken. It was good. Interesting combination of curry chicken on a bed of white rice topped with pickled cucumbers and..... scrambled eggs!! I've never had this before and I consider myself a curry lover and connoisseur.... be it either Indian, Thai or Japanese.... though it wasn't bad at all. The pickled cucumbers were a nice refreshing contrast to the pungent curry. Good variety of flavors, unfortunately nothing spectacular.   It's a place to have a quick bite to eat. I'd go back to try different items from the menu. Very friendly staff.

I don’t know what happened but I first frequented urban belly at the old California ave location and was blown away every time by their noodle soups. Great ingredients but the killer was the wonderful flavorful broth.  somewhere along the line the quality took a hit and it’s just not the same.   Not bad, but something missing. Likewise I used to frequent Belly Shack and while a few of the dishes show up here, it also lost its verve. It’s not that the food is bad, but I know what it could be and miss the old days that got me hooked.
Good stuff

I am a "regular" here so being highly prejudiced when I write this review I have become an "addict" and consider all food items here "comfort" food especially because I am a huge fan of dumplings and good home made broth.  Urban belly has a wonderful, eclectic variety of Pho types of soups which are huge enough in portion to share with a friend and fried rice combinations where you simply order a bowl of rice and combine it with veggies, meats or tofu.  I always come here on a Sunday and relax with a cup of broth, steamed rice, dumplings and sometimes their spicy fries.  Today I tried their home brewed, iced Vietnamese coffee which is a wonderful value because you receive a free refill for the price of one serving.  This restaurant is extremely well run and clean.  All the items on the menu are priced well and delicious.  My only complaint is once in a while young families might bring in a "group" of small children and so it can get quite noisy here if the parents decide not to quiet down their kids.  One time I came here and two groups of children were here to celebrate  a birthday party and the young birthday girl was screeching pretty high and running around on her scooter.  I kind of wonder why parents think this restaurant is suitable for birthday parties?  I truly think the food here is perfect for children but if you are planning on having a party perhaps Urban belly should suggest renting out the entire restaurant for these occasional gatherings because if you are paying for a meal then hopefully the environment should be reasonably peaceful for all diners and not turned into a "playground" for kids.  Other than the families bringing in children I would highly encourage everyone in Wicker Park to enjoy the relaxed atmosphere here and all the waitstaff here is friendly, helpful and good at giving suggestions about what to order.  Every first of the month I was told you can purchase any dumpling for a dollar!  There is also free filtered still or sparkling water you can help yourself to and no one here rushes you in and out so you can relax enjoy the free wifi and not be hurried out the door.  This restaurant is definitely a place I come to relax and enjoy a good view of the neighborhood as people walk past.  Dishes here range from very mild to ultra spicy so you will never grow bored of the menu and the food is consistently great.  This place deserves a Five but I am taking away one star due to the fact that every now and again there are just way too many parents who do not have control over their young children and it kind of ruins the tranquil vibe when you hear screeching kids.  I get the idea that this place is family friendly but kids get bored easily and because there is a kid's menu and the staff never say anything the noise can get pretty bad when there are lots of young children present.  I love coming here but I wish the parents understood this is NOT a Chucky Cheese.   I will continue dining here every time I work or do errands in Wicker Park.  This place has incredibly healthy and tasty food at reasonable prices.  The desserts here are amazing too.  Try the peanut butter and jelly soft serve ice cream!  It's satisfying and decadent. In short: Build-your-own meal concept executed well, with enough variety to cater to cravings but still deliver familiar flavors.  Food: This is one of my favorite casual spots to take friends! Sometimes Asian fusion gets a little heavy, but Urbanbelly does a great job delivering flavors and fresh ingredients to balance out the starchiness of noodles and rice dishes. There’s enough flexibility in the menu to allow you to switch it up when you feel like it, but still get flavors that you know you like. The Chef’s Specials are always changing and really showcases their creativity. Get the Togarashi fries - the curry mayo dipping sauce is SO addicting.  Service: You order at the counter, pay and pick a table to put your number on and your food gets dropped off at the table. Usually pretty timely and what you’d expect from a casual spot, nothing unexpected.

The kimchi stew was at the same time familiar in regard to taste, but unlike any I've had before in terms of actual composition and presentation.
